        "shortName": "AUG 762",
        "description": "Steyr AUG A3 is a 5.56x45 bullpup assault rifle, developed by the Austrian company Steyr-Daimler-Puch. AUG is known for good ergonomics, decent accuracy, low recoil and sufficient reliability. The rifle also stands out for its futuristic design. The A3 version features a bolt-catch button. This rifle has been modified to be compatible with 7.62x39mm caliber ammunition while retaining it's standout characteristics."
